title: topless_other
body:
Nude from the waist up. Not wearing a top, but wearing bottoms. For example, wearing [[pants]] without a [[shirt]].

h6. Guidelines

* Don't use when the character is [[nude]] or [[completely nude]].
* Don't use when you can't see the character's lower body. You should be able to tell the character is wearing bottom clothing. Use [[nude]] instead.
* Don't use if the character is wearing a [[bra]] or [[bikini top only|bikini top]]. Use [[no shirt]] instead.
* Don't use [[bare shoulders]], [[bare back]], or [[bare arms]] with this tag.
* Don't use for [[monster]]s who don't normally wear bottom clothing. Use [[nude]] instead.

h4. See also

* [[bottomless]]
* [[no shirt]]
* [[topless male]]
* [[topless female]]
* [[Tag Group:Sexual Attire]]

title: avalon_le_fae_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Lostbelt No. 6: Fae Round Table Domain, Avalon le Fae[/b]
[quote]
The fierce battle in Olympus ended in Chaldea's victory over the Greek gods, as well as the confirmed simultaneous termination of the sixth Tree of Emptiness. Without the Tree of Emptiness, the sixth Lostbelt ceased to be a threat, leaving only the seventh Lostbelt to conquer.
...Or so it was believed.
But the Observation Lens Sheba projects a different future: the imminent collapse of the planet itself, triggered by the sixth Lostbelt.

There is hardly any time left until the planet's demise.
To prevent this untimely end, Chaldea sets foot in a mystical land inhabited by faeries—the British Lostbelt.
[/quote]
[expand=Part 2]
[quote]
"Chosen by the Staff of Selection, the savior, guarded by travelers from afar, shall reach the throne."

The key to the conquest of Britain is the defeat of Morgan, ruler of the Lostbelt.
The Song of Prophecy foretells her downfall once the Child of Prophecy journeys to ring the six Bells of Pilgrimage, protected by the six clans.
Also mentioned is a foreign mage—Chaldea's Master—who has been witnessed at the Child of Prophecy's side throughout Britain, giving credence to the divination.

Having earned an audience with the High Queen by warding off a Calamity, the party sets their sights on the fae capital—Camelot, the city of sin.
Prophecy and calamity, Faeries and humans.
What end awaits at the crossroads of fate once myriad expectations come into play?
[/quote]
[/expand]
The sixth Lostbelt in [[Fate/Grand Order]], set on the isle of Great Britain and supervised by the Crypter [[Beryl Gut]]. It was released in three parts on the Japanese server on June 11, 2021, July 14, 2021, and August 4 2021, and on the NA server on June 6, 2023, June 20, 2023, and July 10, 2023. [[Habetrot (fate)|]] is given as a reward to players for completing the lostbelt.

title: airani_iofifteen_(work)
body:
The 6th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive Indonesia]]'s [[Airani Iofifteen]]. It has an [[idol]] theme matching with the other members of [[Area 15]].

It consists of a [[white capelet|white]] [[half capelet]], a [[black jacket|black]] [[cropped jacket|cropped]] [[short-sleeved jacket]] with [[puffy short sleeves]], [[white choker]], a [[black shirt|black]] [[halter shirt]] [[crop top]] with [[criss-cross straps]], a [[single glove|single]] [[fingerless gloves|fingerless]] [[black gloves|black glove]] on her right hand, [[bracelet|bracelets]] on her left wrist, [[frilled shorts|frilled]] [[black shorts]] with a [[belly chain]],  [[grey socks|grey]] [[fishnet socks|fishnet]] [[kneehighs]] and [[black footwear|black]] [[lace-up boots]].

Her [[official alternate hairstyle]] for this outfit is a [[high ponytail]] with [[asymmetrical bangs|asymmetrical]] [[braided bangs]] and a [[star hair ornament|star]] [[hairclip]]. In addition, her hair has [[blue hair|blue]] and [[green hair|green]] [[streaked hair|streaks]].

She has a green [[facial mark]] below her right eye, along with some [[star facial mark|star-shaped facial marks]] below and above her eyes, along with [[star in eye|stars in both of her eyes]].

title: toyama_kasumi
body:
The [[electric_guitar|guitarist]] and vocalist of the band [[Poppin'Party]], and main protagonist of [[BanG Dream!]]. She is an energetic and optimistic girl who was inspired by a starlit night to begin playing music. 

She has [[brown hair]] with [[double bun|double]] [[cone hair bun]]s meant to resemble a star (how they work are a mystery, even to other characters), and [[purple eyes]].

She has a younger sister called [[Toyama Asuka]].

Her birthday is July 14th. Her seiyuu is [[Terakawa Aimi]].

[b]Raiding Chariot Dungeon: Celtic Prison[br]Death Jail Summer Escape ~Medb's Prison of Sin and Despair 2017~[/b]
[quote]While each team races through the scorching heat at full throttle, everyone tumbles into a deep ravine just as they're about to cross the finish line.
Master and Mash hurry to investigate and see if the competitors are okay, and learn that all the participants have been thrown in jail!
Can the incarcerated Servants find a way to escape the supposedly inescapable prison?[/quote]

title: dead_heat_summer_race!
body:
[b]Summer Racing Festival: Ishtar Cup[br]Dead Heat Summer Race! ~The Ishtar Cup of Hopes and Dreams 2017~[/b]
[quote]While Master enjoys a well-deserved break with Mash,
Ishtar shows up with a big, too-happy smile.
She informs the pair that she found a new Singularity,
and warns that the world will be in danger if something isn't done.

After stopping Mash from requesting an official Order,
Ishtar mentions a certain ritual of her devising to eliminate the Singularity.
A summer festival to get everyone all fired up will be just the thing to deal with this Singularity...

That's right...the only option is to hold a cross country race![/quote]

title: all_the_statesmen!
body:
[b]All the Statesmen! Learning with Manga: The History of the American Frontier[/b]
[quote]Emergency! Emergency! Crisis in Chaldea!
The Master, their Servants, and even the staff have been affected by a sudden onset of total worthlessness!
The Main Character must Rayshift to the singularity that is the source of this terrible plague: North America during the Western Expansion.
A fearsome threat looms over the continent, and the Main Character faces their toughest battle yet.
In their moment of need, aid comes in the most unlikely form, who turns out to be none other than...!?[/quote]
!asset #25187373

title: se.ra.ph_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Abyssal Cyber Paradise, SE.RA.PH[/b]
[quote]
"A resort event? You thought this would be a walk on the beach?
Welcome, all you foolish Masters!
The fate of the world rests in your silly, useless hands♥"

Our stage will be the Offshore Oil Rig, Seraphix, now a hellish recreation of the Moon Grail War.
This is a cage of ecstasy from which only one can escape.
Only moments remain until the base disintegrates.
And what is it that lurks at the bottom of this dance of Egos...?
[/quote]
[expand=Original Description]
[quote]
"Spring break means it's time for a trip!
It's a little early, but how about a beach event, foolish humans?"
The sudden arrival of the demonic digital brain BB throws Chaldea into a chaotic spring vacation.
A sweet, heated catfight ensues.
Fragile, pure, and sexy...
Look forward to an unforgettable resort event!
[/quote]
[/expand]

The extra pseudo-singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]], set in the [[Chaldea Security Organization]]'s Seraphix oil rig, which has been displaced into the Mariana Trench in 2030 and transformed into a space resembling the Moon Cell from [[Fate/EXTRA CCC]]. It was initially presented as a collaboration event between Fate/Grand Order and Fate/EXTRA CCC, only to be revealed as a pseudo-singularity upon the event releasing.

Released on the Japanese server on May 1, 2017 and on the NA server on April 23, 2019. [[BB (fate/extra)|]] is given as a reward to players for completing the event. It was adapted into a manga by [[Nishiide Kengorou]].

We'll have surprises all night on a special stage made just for this occasion - Alluring Castle Csetje!

All the staff here will welcome you every night with smiles, so please come play with me every day and every night, all right? ♥
Or else, I'm just going to eat cake by myself.

What? You're asking about the cute girl with the lovely voice? Well then, you'll have to find out when you get here!
[/quote]
A limited time [[Halloween]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on October 21, 2015 and on the NA server on October 17, 2017. [[Elizabeth Bathory (Halloween Caster) (fate)|]] is given to players as a reward for completing the event.

title: kasane_teto
body:
A [[UTAU]] character with [[red hair|red]] [[twin drills]].

She is a young girl with [[red eyes]] and [[red hair|red]] [[twin drills]]. She typically wears a dark blue/gray outfit with red trim. Her official profile lists her as a "chimera", so she is sometimes given characteristics like a forked tail or wings. Her character item is a [[baguette]]. 

She was created as an April Fools joke by the VIPPERs of 2ch, meant to trick Nico-Nico Douga users into thinking she was the 3rd Vocaloid from Crypton. After the joke was over, instead of fading into obscurity Teto was picked up by [[UTAU]], a freeware knock-off of [[VOCALOID]]. She has maintained a level of popularity, and many have tried to replicate this effect with other joke and fanmade characters since.

After her 15th anniversary on April 2023, she received an [[kasane teto (sv)|updated voicebank]] under the [[Synthesizer V]] engine, which would boost her popularity even further.

Her voice provider is [[Oyamano Mayo]].

Oyamano initially used the name Oyama Nobuyo as a reference to famed singer and voice actress [[Ooyama Nobuyo]]. Since the latter is most known as the voice of [[Doraemon (character)|]], fans had Teto share similar traits. Teto's [[catchphrase]] 君は実に馬鹿だな ("You really are an idiot, aren't you?") also originated from a [[Doraemon]] comic.

Do not tag Kasane Teto as a [[VOCALOID]]. She is either an UTAU or a SynthV.

She is an [[oni]] with [[skin-covered horns]], [[red eyes]], a [[fang]] and [[long hair|long]] [[white hair|white]] or [[grey hair]] with a [[red hair|red]] [[gradient hair|gradient]] and [[streaked hair|streaks]]. title: cropped
body:
An image that is a cropped portion of a larger picture. 

It's not uncommon for artists on Twitter to post both the full-size picture and a crop, in order to play around twitter's cropping mechanism. Sometimes the cropped version is of higher resolution than the equivalent portion of the full picture, in which case it makes sense to upload both images. 
Generally, you should make the cropped post the child post, even if it is of higher resolution than the uncropped post.

It is also possible that the full size image is only available as a [[paid reward available ]].

h4.See also

* [[duplicate]]
* [[paid reward available]]
* [[third-party edit]]
* [[Tag Group:Image Composition]]

title: sister_teto
body:
A derivative of [[UTAU]] [[Kasane Teto]] as a [[nun]], created by [[Sidai Rusk uu]].

The artist also made a short [[animated]] version consisting of a [[fake screenshot]] with [[dialogue box|dialogue]] and asked fans to make music to go along with it. Many fans did so but the most prominent version was made by [[Haibara Memory]]. Their song ended up being expanded to a [[confession to sister (synthesizer v)|full length Synthizer V song]] with a music video animated by Sidai Rusk uu.

* !post #7910469: Original work
* !post #8524805: Animated version (post #8524805)
* !post #8525184: Sung version by Haibara Memory (post #8525184)

h4. See also
* [[Confession to Sister (Synthesizer V)]]
* [[List of vocal synth derivatives]]

title: list_of_project_diva_modules
body:
This is a list of all tagged module in the [[project diva (series)|Hatsune Miku -Project DIVA-]] series of rhythm games, listed in alphabetical order.

Modules are the [[official alternate costume|costumes]] available for the characters in the games. They can be associated with specific songs, be part of a series, or be a standalone design. As with other Vocaloid [[list_of_Vocaloid_derivatives|derivatives]], artists tend to portray each module as their own individual person (See post #1049414 for example).

title: xaihi_(arknights)
body:
A playable operator in [[arknights:_endfield|Arknights: Endfield]].

[quote]
Few people could immediately identify Xaihi's origins upon their first meeting with her. But the girl's occasional display of "Lateran vibes" would quickly reveal her affiliation with the Cabal of Tranquility.

Xaihi possesses a vast and seemingly trivial knowledge of many fields, especially those pertaining to information technology. During talks, she tends to jump from one strange topic to the next—a habit that one must get used to if they wish to converse with her. Xaihi herself, however, is utterly unaware of these issues.
[/quote]

title: luigi
body:
[b]Luigi[/b] is [[Mario]]'s younger, but taller, twin brother. 

Luigi has assisted and fought alongside his brother on many occasions. Throughout his life, he has lived in Mario's shadow, developing both cowardly and heroic tendencies. [[Mario Bros.]] marks his first appearance in a Super Mario  arcade game. Originally a color swap of Mario, Luigi was created to facilitate a second player option. Since the two player mode was dropped from most [[Mario (series)|Super Mario]] games beginning with Super Mario Land, Luigi had gained his own identity and personality.

title: mario
body:
[b]Mario[/b] ([b]マリオ[/b]) is the main protagonist of the [[mario (series)|Mario series]], the legendary mascot of [[Nintendo]], and basically the video game equivalent of [[Mickey Mouse]]. 

Mario is normally a [[plumber]], but in games, he uses his legendary [[jumping]] and combat abilities to defend the inhabitants of the usually peaceful Mushroom World from power-hungry villains such as [[Bowser]]. During most of his adventures, he often teams up with his brother [[Luigi]] and their partner [[Yoshi]] for extra support, as they are the only two characters he fully trusts to help him. When not adventuring, Mario participates in a variety of [[playing sports|sporting events]] and even works as one of his alter-egos, [[Dr. Mario]].

title: yoshi
body:
The [[dinosaur]]-like creatures appearing in the [[Mario_(series)|Mario]] series since [[Super Mario World]], as well as their own series of games. Has a [[frog]]-like tongue which can be used to swallow enemies and turn them into [[yoshi egg|eggs]] which can be thrown. They also all can rapidly kick their feet to gain more height mid-air, called a Flutter Jump.

They come in a multitude of colors, with green being the default.

title: tiny_wario
body:
A depowered form of [[Wario]]. 

In [i][[Wario Land: Super Mario Land 3]][/i] & [i][[Virtual Boy Wario Land]][/i], Wario becomes this when damaged by an enemy and can no longer do his usual attacks like the Shoulder Bash. In [i][[Wario Land II]][/i] it's one of his many transformations, inflicted by a [[Wizard (wario)|]]. Despite losing many of his attacks, it allows him to jump higher and squeeze through small crevices. In [i][[WarioWare]]: Smooth Moves[/i], Wario is accidentally separated into a plethora of multiple Tiny Warios by a motorcycle given by [[Penny Crygor]].

As the name suggests Tiny Wario is smaller in stature compared to regular Wario, often lacks his usual grin and doesn't wear a hat, revealing his [[bald]] head or a [[mohawk]]. In the WarioWare series instead of the shirt and overalls he wears a yellow [[singlet]] with [[yellow gloves]] and [[blue footwear|blue shoes]].

h4. Appearance

title: gundam_zz
body:
[b][i]Gundam ZZ[/i][/b] is the 1986 sequel to [i][[Zeta Gundam]][/i]. It was created by a mostly new creative staff, with series creator [[Tomino Yoshiyuki]] being the main returning member. The first half of [i]Gundam ZZ[/i] is infamous for being significantly more comedy-oriented than previous and subsequent [[Gundam]] series. However, the tone of the series changes and becomes more serious in the second half, concluding the story of Zeta.

ZZ is set in the year [b]Universal Century 0088[/b], beginning almost immediately after the end of [i]Zeta Gundam[/i] (and the final battle of The Gryps War). It follows the story of [[Judau Ashta]], [[pilot]] of the [[AEUG]] [[ZZ Gundam|MSZ-010 ZZ (Double Zeta) Gundam]], during [b]The First [[Neo Zeon]] War[/b], a conflict originated due to [[Haman Karn]]'s declaration of war on the now weakened [[Earth Federation]].

Gundam ZZ is notable because it is the first Gundam series where an underage group of pilots ([i]The [[Gundam Team]][/i]) operate more than two different types of Gundams. This trope would be used years later in other very popular Gundam series like [[Gundam Wing]] in the mid 90s and [[Gundam 00]] the next decade.

The story of ZZ continues in [[Char's Counterattack]].

His mecha of choice are the [[Gundam Mk II]], the [[Hizack]], the [[Galbaldy Beta]] the [[Marasai]], the [[Gabthley]]. the [[Byalant]] and the [[Baund Doc]]. [spoilers]Dies at the end of The Gryps War in battle against Kamille Bidan's [[zeta_gundam_(mobile_Suit)|Zeta Gundam]] who threw his Baund Doc towards the wreckage of the recently destroyed [i][[henken_bekkener|Radish]][/i] [[AEUG]] [[military]] [[spacecraft]].[/spoilers]

title: magazine_(weapon)
body:
A device used for storing [[ammunition]] and feeding it into a repeating [[gun|firearm]]. May be referred to as a "mag" for short. Found in internal as well as external types, the most common is the detachable box magazine, such as that used by most modern [[assault_rifle|assault rifles]] and semi-automatic [[handgun]]s. Magazines generally have [[spring (object)|spring]]-like object inside that pushes ammunition into the chamber.

Not to be confused with a [[clip_(weapon)|]], a simple strip that store multiple rounds together as a unit for [[reloading]] into the fixed magazine or cylinder of a firearm.

h4. See also

* [[ammunition belt]]
* [[ammunition pouch]]
* [[bandolier]]
* [[cartridge]]
* [[clip (weapon)]]
* [[drum magazine]]

title: amane_konata
body:
[[Amane Kanata]]'s "younger sister", first appearing on Kanata's 2025 [[April Fools]] stream.

Her appearance is very similar to Kanata, with both of them having [[grey hair]], [[purple eyes]], a shuriken/[[star halo|star-shaped halo]] and [[mini wings|small]]  [[feathered wings|feathered]] [[angel wings]]. The main differences are that Konata has [[black hair|black]] [[streaked hair]], her [[colored inner hair]] is [[purple hair|purple]] instead of blue, her halo is [[black halo|black]] and her wings [[gradient wings|gradient]] goes from [[white wings|white]] to [[black wings|black]], not to mention being much more [[large breasts|well endowed]] than her sister.

Her default costume is a [[black sweater|black]] [[turtleneck sweater|turtleneck]] [[aran sweater|aran]] [[virgin killer sweater]] with [[cleavage cutout|cleavage]] and [[shoulder cutout]]s (although it's sometimes depicted as a [[sleeveless turtleneck]] with [[detached sleeves]]), [[black thighhighs]] and [[black shoes]].

Her hairstyle is based on Kanata's hairstyle from her [[amane kanata (work)|Work costume]], being [[long hair]] in a [[two side up]] held with [[black ribbon|black]] [[hair ribbon]]s witha [[single hair intake]] and long [[asymmetrical bangs]] [[hair over one eye|covering her right eye]].

title: deltarune
body:
[i]Deltarune[/i] is a game by [i][[Undertale]][/i] creator [[Toby Fox]] that was revealed as an unannounced surprise on October 31, 2018, with its first chapter released on that day and the second on September 17, 2021, each for free. It is planned to have several chapters.

title: yoshikawa_chinatsu
body:
[[Yuru Yuri]]

A pink-haired girl in [[Akaza Akari]]'s class who originally wanted to join the school's Tea Ceremony club, but ended up joining the Amusement club because the Tea Ceremony club was abolished. She is often chased after by [[Toshinou Kyouko]] due to her resemblance to [[Mirakurun]], though she herself has a passionate crush on [[Funami Yui]]. She acts cute, especially in the presence of Yui, but she sometimes shows dark thoughts and terrifying artistic skills.

She has an older sister named [[Yoshikawa Tomoko]].

title: protagonist_(lost_property_control_organization)
body:
The technically unnamed (see Post #8567548 and Post #6901257), [[amnesia|amnesiac]] protagonist of [[Samidare (Hoshi)]]'s [[horror (theme)|]] [[video game|game]] concept series, [[Lost Property Control Organization (samidare)|]]. She has [[short hair|short]], [[black hair]], [[aqua eyes]], and wears a pair of thin, [[white ribbon]]s [[hair ribbon|in her hair]] on both sides of her head. Her hairstyle can be changed during character creation and gameplay. She wears a [[school uniform]] while working undercover.

Images that are chronologically early in the series depict her using a [[rust|rusty]] [[lead pipe|pipe]] for a weapon, while images from further down the timeline have her using a [[baseball bat]] wrapped in [[barbed wire]], a [[handgun]], [[spiked knuckles|spiked]] [[brass knuckles]], a [[stun gun]], a trick [[umbrella]], a [[golf club]], a [[sledgehammer]], [[bug spray]], or a [[harpoon]], depicting [[gameplay mechanics|upgrades]] or sidegrades that a player would make to their gear as they progress.

She is accompanied by a [[floating|hovering]] [[drone]], [[T-6407j (samidare)|]], and wears a [[hooded coat]] or [[hooded jacket|jacket]] while on missions.

Her gender is decided during character creation, with one possible male version being shown here.
* !post #9055767

[spoiler]In one ending of the game, she becomes Lost Property 774 after defeating [[lost property 004 (samidare)|Lost Property 004]].[/spoiler]

title: alternate_language
body:
An image that has been hard-translated to another language (usually English) by the artist themselves, or by someone authorized by the artist (the company officially publishing a localization, a translator with the permission of the artist, etc).

In most cases the artist posts the translated version alongside the original version. In some cases the official translation may be poor quality, even though it was sanctioned by the artist.

This is different from [[hard-translated]], which is generally done by [[third-party_edit|third parties]].

title: kilowattrel
body:
[[pokemon (creature)|Pokémon]] #941 in the National Pokédex, an Electric/Flying type.

This [[bird]] Pokémon is predominantly black and yellow in color, with a long curved beak, a large wingspan, and a throat sac. It is based on a frigatebird, a type of seabird.

It evolves from [[Wattrel]].

Its shiny form solely changes its black features into a purple-red color.

title: ceruledge
body:
[[pokemon (creature)|Pokémon]] #937 in the National Pokédex, a Fire/Ghost type.

This tall humanoid Pokémon is predominantly purple and black in color, with fire blazing from its head. It has sword-like extensions stemming from its forearms. It also has [[purple eyes]] and [[white pupils]].

It is one of the evolutions [[Charcadet]] can achieve, the other being [[Armarouge]].

Its shiny form turns its eyes [[red eyes|red]] and pupils [[yellow pupils|yellow]].

title: pearl_harbor
body:
[b]Pearl Harbor[/b] is a natural harbor and [[United States Navy]] base on the [[Hawaii]]an island of Oahu. It was the site of "the 7 December 1941 attack":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attack_on_Pearl_Harbor by [[Japan]]ese naval and air forces that brought the [[United States]] into [[World War II]].

h4.See also

title: uss_arizona_(bb-39)
body:
The [b]USS Arizona (BB-39)[/b] was the second and last of the Pennsylvania-class [[battleship]] built for the [[United States Navy]]. The ship was laid down in 1914 and commissioned two years later in 1916.

Arizona is infamously known as the only battleship that was lost to the [[Imperial Japanese Navy]] during the Attack on [[Pearl Harbor]] on 7 December 1941. While the other battleships were recovered after the attack, Arizona suffered a magazine detonation that completely destroyed the ship. After the war, the [[USS Arizona Memorial]] was built over its wreck.

title: uss_arizona_memorial
body: A war memorial built atop of the [[shipwreck]] of the American [[battleship]] [[USS Arizona (BB-39)]] located in [[Pearl Harbor]], [[Hawaii]], [[United States]].

title: dungeon_crusaderz
body:
A [[dungeon]] [[eroge]] RPG game by Atelier Kaguya TEAM HEART BEAT with illustrations by [[M&M]]. The game released on December 15, 2006 and shares characters from [[Magical Witch Academy]]. Its sequel is [[Dungeon Crusaderz 2]].

Japanese Title: ダンジョンクルセイダーズ

h4. Game Synopsis
Cliff, who is possessed by "Devil Power", is on a journey with [[cecilia_wainsearth|Cecilia]], who is also possessed by "Devil Soul". Their destination is Rouleburg, a fortress city. There is a treasure they look for in a huge basement dungeon under Rouleburg. Cliff wants it to get "Devil Power", and Cecilia needs it to remove "Devil Soul". They meet various girls along the way, at a bar or a shop, and the adventure to the basement dungeon starts now...

h4. Characters
* [[Ayame Neuendorf]]
* [[Cecilia Wainsearth]]
* [[Claudia Krausses]]
* [[Erika Rouleburg]]
* [[Ferue It]]
* [[iris_(dungeon_crusaderz)|Iris]] (Also appears in Magical Witch Academy)
* [[Kamira]]
* [[karen_(dungeon_crusaderz)|Karen]]

title: dungeon_crusaderz_2
body:
A dungeon [[eroge]] RPG game by Atelier Kaguya TEAM HEART BEAT with illustrations by [[M&M]]. The game released on December 19, 2008 and shares characters from [[Magical Witch Academy]]. It's the sequel to [[Dungeon Crusaderz]].

Japanese Title: ダンジョンクルセイダーズ2~永劫の楽土~

h4. Game Synopsis
There is a [[city]] called Glaciest at the northern edge of the continent. The city is famous for a mysterious phenomenon in which people's dream realizes and a crystallized dream called Evil Ice Stone. Glaciest is always full of people who come to see the stone or to investigate the phenomenon. Also, there is a rumor that a lot of treasures are hidden inside a tower, Horn of Revelia, and the top of the tower is connected to a promised land, Eternal Paradise. Allion is a member of a special group that is organized to mediate wars between countries. One day, he and his company are ordered to visit Glaciest. With different purposes in their minds, their adventure now starts...

title: the_o_(mobile_suit)
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in [[Zeta Gundam]] from 1985.

The [b]PMX-003 The O[/b] is [[Paptimus Scirocco]]'s personal [[mobile suit]]. Its colossal size and girth deceivingly hide its impressive maneuverability, courtesy of countless [[vernier thrusters]] of various sizes all over the unit. 

As if that wasn't enough, it loads a massively powerful [[beam rifle]], as well as two [[extra arms]] hidden in the front skirt that can wield beam sabers of their own and overwhelm enemy units in combat. 

For defense, it has a thick armor (which gave the MS its known size as said above) which can withstand both solid and beam weaponry[spoiler], but not [[watermelon bar]]s[/spoiler].

h4. See also
* [[Xeku Eins]] - A mass produced MS with a similar design.
* [[Over.On]]

body:
An alternate universe variant of [[Tails (Sonic)|]] who appears in the animated series [i][[Sonic Prime]][/i]. In this series, the multiverse is fractured, leading to the creation of various alternate realities. Sails Tails is from the "No Place" dimension, a pirate-themed reality. In this world, he is a member of [[Knuckles the Dread]]'s pirate crew aboard the Angel's Voyage.

Physically, Sails Tails resembles the original Tails, being an anthropomorphic fox with two tails. However, he sports a pirate-themed outfit, including brown gloves and boots, a white bandanna with blue stripes over his right ear, a brown vest, and a brown belt equipped with a mechanical arm, reflecting his role as a pirate.

title: tails_(sonic)
body:
[b]Miles "Tails" Prower[/b] is [[Sonic the Hedgehog]]'s orange fox sidekick and long time friend. His name is a pun on "miles per hour", but he prefers to go by his nickname "Tails". 

He has two tails that he uses for flying like a helicopter, and is just as smart as [[Dr. Eggman]] when it comes to robotics. He's able to build and fly his own planes like the Tornado.

His voice actors are Hayashi Kazuki (1998-1999), Murata Atsuki (2000-2001), and [[Hirohashi Ryou]] (since 2003) in Japanese.

Voiced by Connor Bringas, Corey Bringas, Amy Palent, [[Kate Higgins]], and Colleen Villard in English. 

Among the cast of Sonic characters, Tails has received the most voice changes.

title: dwadge
body:
A fictional manned giant battle robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in [[Gundam MSV]]. 

[b]MS-09G Dwadge[/b]

A modification of the [[Dom (mobile suit)|]] [[mobile_suit|MS]] intended as a specialist unit for desert operations, it is the final production model of all the Dom series. 

As well as the added dust proofing and dust filters, the units received head Vulcans, a refitted hard point for the heat saber on the backpack and a large [[Heat Hawk]] placed on the back of the waist when not in use. 

Some units carried rocket grenades that could be locked and thrown into the air towards their targets. While they weren't used in [[mobile_suit_gundam|The One Year War]], many units remained in hiding with [[Zeon]] remnants on Earth, being deployed by [[Neo Zeon]] in [[gundam _zz|The First Neo Zeon War]] and [[gundam_unicorn|the Third Neo Zeon War]] to great effect in desert operations.

h4. See also
* [[Dwadge Custom]]
* [[Pezun Dwadge]]

title: dom_(mobile_suit)
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] from 1979.

[b]MS-09B Dom[/b]

[[Mobile Suit]] fielded by the Principality of [[Zeon]] during [[mobile_suit_gundam|"The One Year War"]]. 

Designed from scratch as a land combat MS, the Dom differs from its predecessor, the [[Zaku II]], in its revised and much more resistent armor and its added maneuverability courtesy of extra [[vernier thrusters]] in its feet, which allow it to "hover" along the ground. 

The design was later revised for use in [[space]] combat, and entered service as the [[rick_dom| MS-09R Rick Dom.]]

title: the_looney_tunes_show
body: The Looney Tunes Show is an American animated sitcom produced by Warner Bros. Animation, and aired on [[Cartoon Network]] for two seasons from May 3, 2011, to November 2, 2013. The series featured characters from the [[Looney Tunes]] and Merrie Melodies theatrical cartoon shorts in a sitcom format with [[Bugs Bunny]] and [[Daffy Duck]], who live a suburban life together within a neighborhood of fellow cartoon neighbors, dealing with various issues in their own way. Many episodes also include a musical short under the Merrie Melodies name, and the first season also includes computer-animated shorts involving new antics between [[Wile E Coyote]] and the [[Road Runner (looney tunes)|]].

title: fear_&_hunger_1
body:
An indie survival horror dungeon-crawler video game with RPG elements created by Miro Haverinen.

The player is tasked with guiding one of four protagonists through a mysterious dungeon located in the fantasy kingdom of Rondon. Although each protagonist arrives for different reasons, they will all be forced to face the turmoil and darkness of the depths to accomplish those goals.

The game is notorious for both its difficulty and extremely graphic violence and occasional graphic sexual violence.

It has a direct sequel in [[Fear & Hunger 2: Termina]], set 300 years after the events of Fear & Hunger.

title: haman_karn
body:
Antagonist female character from [i][[Zeta Gundam]][/i] and [i][[Gundam ZZ]][/i]. An intelligent, calculating, cold, cruel and evil beautiful woman, she is the regent to [[Mineva Lao Zabi]] and de facto leader of [[Neo Zeon]]. 

Haman pilots the [[mobile suit]]s [[Gaza-C]] and the [[Qubeley]]. [spoilers]A powerful Newtype, Haman Karn dies during a pivotal [[space]] [[battle]] duel against [[Judau Ashta]] in his [[ZZ Gundam]] at the end of Gundam ZZ.[/spoilers]

She is also featured heavily in [[Char's Deleted Affair]] as a teenager, and an [[office lady]] AU version of her is the protagonist of [[Arasa OL Haman-sama]].

Haman's peculiar hairstyle was based on "this photo":https://www.pinterest.com/pin/37788084359430218/.

title: egg_hammer
body:
One of Dr. Eggman’s robotic creations—a heavy, [[hammer]]-wielding Badnik that appears in several instalments of the [[Sonic (series)|Sonic the Hedgehog series]].

Compared to the smaller [[Egg Pawn]], an Egg Hammer is much larger, heavily armored, and equipped with a massive, spike-adorned hammer. These Badniks are characterized by their imposing size and brute strength—even though they move slowly.

Their design typically includes a rounded, armored torso with distinctive color schemes (often incorporating purples, reds, grays, and blacks) along with large hands and feet to better handle their weapon.

title: no_russian_(meme)
body:
"No Russian" is an infamous level from the 2009 [[video game]] [[Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2]] in which the player partakes in a [[terrorist]] attack which involves shooting at and killing unarmed civilians at a Russian [[Airport]].

Before committing the [[massacre]], the main antagonist [[vladimir_r_makarov|Vladimir Makarov]] said [b]"Remember – no Russian"[/b] to the player (an undercover American special force member) as they were about to get out of the [[elevator]]. In the original context, the phase was meant to instruct his followers to only speak in English to hide their Russian identity (and therefore put the blame of the operation onto the American-affiliated groups). However, the quote "No Russian" has been misattributed into Makarov instructing his followers into killing any Russian they come across, therefore it has been used as a "snowclone":[https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/snowclone] on the internet.

The mission drew controversy in the media for its portrayal of a terrorist attack which the player can choose to partake in. Because of the nature of the mission, it can be skipped entirely without impeding the game progression.

h4. External links

* "Know Your Meme: No Russian / Remember - no Russian":[https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/no-russian-remember-no-russian]
* "Wikipedia: No Russian":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/No_Russian

title: fading
body:
When a character is gradually vanishing into nothingness. Typically rendered as the person being partially [[transparent]] or parts of the body disappearing from one end to the other. This tag may require context and be subjective.

* Not to be confused with [[projected inset]], when a character is inset at a lower opacity for dramatic or comedic effect.

* Not to be confused with [[zoom layer]], where an image has a semi-transparent, upscaled version in the background.

If a person seems to be merely drawn as translucent, rather than actually being so (such as for the sake of showing something behind them), then tag as [[x-ray]] instead.

* Consider using [[dissolving]] instead if a character is becoming incorporated into a [[liquid]] or [[smoke]].

title: colt_m1877
body:
The Colt Model 1877 was a double-action [[revolver]] with very similar dimensions to the more famous [[Colt Single Action Army]], though can be visually distinguished by its larger trigger guard and curved handle. It was a favored weapon of figures such as Billy the Kid, John Wesley Hardin, and John Henry "Doc" Holliday.

Despite users of such pedigree, the Model 1877's double-action system was extremely delicate and frequently broke, turning the gun into a single-action where the hammer and trigger had to be manually operated. Much like the SAA, the Model 1877 was never made capable of using smokeless gunpowder, and late in its life had to carry large warnings to use black gunpowder only.

In anime, the Model 1877 is most commonly seen used by [[Billy the Kid (fate)|]] in [[Fate/Grand Order]].

title: white_army
body:
The [b]Russian White Army[/b] (also known as the White Guard or White Movement) refers to a loose confederation of anti-Bolshevik forces that fought against the [[soviet army|Red Army]] during the [[Russian Civil War]] (1917–1923). Emerging after the [[October Revolution]], the White Army was composed of monarchists, conservatives, liberals, and other factions united by their opposition to the Bolsheviks. Unlike their unified opponents, the Whites lacked a single cohesive ideology or leadership, which contributed to their eventual defeat.

The White Movement began forming in 1917 as resistance to the Bolshevik seizure of power. Key leaders included Admiral [[Alexander Kolchak]], General [[Anton Denikin]], and General [[Pyotr Wrangel]]. Operating across vast regions like Siberia, South Russia, and the Far East, the Whites received support from foreign powers such as the Allied Intervention forces (e.g., Britain, France, and the United States). Despite early successes, internal divisions, corruption, and lack of popular support led to their collapse by 1923.

h4. Symbolism

The term "White" contrasts with the "Red" of the Bolsheviks, drawing from historical Russian symbolism where white represented purity and loyalty to the Tsar. The Whites often used the double-headed eagle and the tricolor flag (white, blue, red) of the Russian Empire as their emblems.

h4. See also

* [[Soviet Army|Red Army]]
* [[Imperial Russian Army]]
* [[Russian Empire]]

title: qujupao
body:
The qujupao is a style of [[hanfu]] that was worn as informal wear during the Spring & Autumn Period, Warring States, Qin, and Han Dynasties. It's construction is that of a long wrap-around [[robe]] with a y-shaped collar and a [[sash]] around the waist or hips. Its hem is curved, this detail distinguishes it from the [[zhijupao]], which has a straight hem. These two styles are reffered to as "shenyi" and could be worn by any gender.

Shenyi could be confused to be [[kimono]], but shenyi is really the predecessor to kimono, which it was influenced by. 

h4. Examples

* !post #7544053
H4. Comparison
* !post #8763813: left: [[kimono]], right: qujupao

title: holding
body:
Someone is holding an object.

This tag should only be used for items you can pick up and carry with your hands. Don't use for holding body parts (like [[holding hands]], or [[breast hold|holding someone's breasts]]), or for holding clothing being worn (like a [[skirt hold]]), or for holding things with something other than the hands (like a [[mouth hold]], [[holding with feet]], or [[holding with tail]]).

To search for something specific being held, just use two tags together, like this: {{holding popsicle}}. Note that these searches don't always work well. Many posts of a search like {{holding hat}} are people [i]wearing hats[/i] while [i]holding other things[/i], so it would be ineffective to see people [i]holding hats[/i]. Hence the existence of specialized tags.

title: johnny_joestar
body:
One of the main protagonists of [[Steel Ball Run]], alongside [[Gyro Zeppeli]]. A paraplegic former horse jockey that resolves to follow [[Gyro Zeppeli]] in the Steel Ball Run race, hoping he may hold the key to letting him walk again.

His [[stand (jojo)|Stand]] power is [[Tusk (Stand)|Tusk]]. Wears a hat with a horse head/horseshoe emblem on the front.

Most of the time he wears: [[Hoodie]] with [[short sleeves]] and [[heart ornament]] on them, [[beanie]] with [[horseshoe hat ornament]] and [[star print|print of stars]] on beanie, pants and wristband, horse head print. In winter location he wear hoodie with [[long sleeves]] and [[feathers]] in [[hood]]. In both suits he wears pants with [[star print]]. 
But in anime he wear [[blue pants]] without [[star print]] and fused with boots, [[white beanie]] with print of horse head and [[horseshoe hat ornament]], [[white hoodie]] with purple line on them, blue [[heart ornament]] on short [[two-tone sleeves]] and [[american flag]] stylized [[wristband]]
other_names: ジョニィ・ジョースター

title: quackity
body:
Mexican streamer and Youtuber. These days, streams in both Spanish and English and makes mostly [[Minecraft YouTube|Minecraft]] content. Has played characters on the [[Dream SMP]] and [[Karmaland]]; founded and plays on the [[Quackity SMP]].

In Dream SMP, he was the vice president of Manberg under [[Jschlatt]]'s rule, with the two being entangled in a toxic romantic relationship. He would later go on to get engaged to [[Karl Jacobs]] and [[Sapnap]], but would become estranged from them and instead focus his attention on his new casino nation, Las Nevadas, recruiting various members for the new faction and training [[Slimecicle]] as his successor.

h4. Appearance
Quackity is usually drawn as a man with [[black hair]] who wears a blue [[beanie]]. While his Minecraft skins have a pale skintone, fanart often depicts him with a slightly darker skintone.

h5. Skins
* !asset #22469128: Default

title: patriotism
body:
Posts that pay tribute and/or glorify a certain country or nation, real or fictional, regardless of whether the post is genuine or simply [[satire]]. Post with patriotism motif usually features the country's national [[flag]], [[map]], [[military]], or other symbols associated with that country in particular. 

Note that posts that featuring character wearing national [[flag print]] clothing or merely featuring the national [[flag]] is not sufficient to qualify for this tag. Other aforementioned symbolism mentioned above should also be present to emphasize the country or nation in question.

h4. See also

* [[propaganda]]
* pool #11772: Extreme Patriotism

h4. External links

* Wikipedia: "Nationalism":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nationalism] & "Patriotism":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patriotism]

title: no_to_ai_generated_images_(alexander_nanitchkov)
body:
Posts referencing a certain viral image featuring a [[no symbol]] over the word AI, with a caption reading "No to AI generated images" as a statement against [[AI-generated]] images. The logo was originally designed by [[Alexander Nanitchkov]], though the original upload has since been removed from his account.

The image was posted en masse to ArtStation, [[DeviantArt]], and [[Pixiv]] in protest of those sites' announcements that they would not ban [[AI-generated]] art. The image later spread to [[Lofter]], after the site announced they would be launching an image generation feature.

h4. Original Version
* !asset #7318081

h4. See also
* [[ai-generated art (topic)]]

title: cloth_(hollow_knight)
body: An NPC in [[Hollow Knight]], [b]Cloth[/b] is a [[club]]-wielding [[cicada]] warrior who, despite her cowardice, traveled to Hallownest to prove her courage [spoilers]and die in battle to reunite with her deceased friend Nola. If certain conditions are met, she will fight alongside the [[Knight (hollow knight)|]] against the Traitor Lord, giving her own life to land the finishing blow.[/spoilers]

title: akami_chiyo
body:
Spanish-speaking [[indie virtual youtuber|Independent]] [[fish girl|Piranha]]-themed [[virtual youTuber]]. Former member of [[Amai Direct]]'s second generation.

She has [[two-tone hair|two-tone]] [[medium hair]], mainly [[black hair]] with [[red hair|red]] [[colored inner hair]], arranged in a [[two side up]]. She also has [[red eyes]], one central [[head fins|head fin]], and a [[red tail|red]] and [[black tail|black]] [[fish tail]] with two [[tail piercing|piercings]].

Her original outfit consists of a [[black dress|black]] & [[red dress|red]] [[gradient dress|gradient]] [[pleated dress]] with a [[turtleneck dress|turtleneck]], [[wide sleeves]] and a [[black bowtie]]; black [[boots]]; [[gradient legwear|gradient]] [[black thighhighs|black]] and [[red thighhighs]], and [[legwear garter]]s.

Her second outfit includes a [[white shirt]] with [[fishnet sleeves]], and her [[clothes writing|name]] and a [[fish skeleton]] [[fish print|printed]] on it; a [[multicolored skirt|multicolored]] [[black skirt|black]] & [[red skirt]] fastened by a [[white belt]]; [[uneven legwear|uneven]] [[white socks]]; and [[black footwear|black]] & [[red footwear|red]] sneakers, and a [[fish hair ornament]].

h4. External Links
* "YouTube":[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCH_31p7pdpTNJXmZmtMMuvg]
* "Twitch":[https://www.twitch.tv/akamichiyo]
* "Twitter":[https://twitter.com/AkamiChiyo]
* "Virtual YouTuber Wiki: Akami Chiyo":[https://virtualyoutuber.fandom.com/wiki/Akami_Chiyo]

title: mikotsuhime_(funamusea)
body:
Character from [[Oounabara to Wadanohara]]

Has [[long hair|long]] [[blue hair|blue]] or [[black hair]] worn in [[twintails]]. She wears a [[kimono]] and has a [[fish skeleton]] in her [[hair ornament|hair]].

title: kipfel_(vrchat)
body:
[[kipfel_(vrchat)|Kipfel]] is an original 3D character by [[Mochiyama Kingyo]] for [[VRChat]].

She features [[animal ears]] and a [[tail]], complemented by her [[very long hair|very long]] [[grey hair]] and [[green eyes]]. On her head, she wears a [[black hat|black]] [[beanie]] designed to resemble a [[cat hat]], adorned with a [[fish skeleton]] decoration. She is also seen with a [[black necktie]].

For her upper body, she dons a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[green shirt]], topped with a [[green sweater]] [[sweater vest|vest]]. Her lower attire consists of a [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[black skirt]]. There is a [[bandaid]] on her left knee, and [[black footwear|black]] [[lace-up boots]] on her feet.

title: fish_skeleton
body: The [[skeleton]] of a [[fish]].

title: bretta_(hollow_knight)
body: NPC in [[Hollow Knight]]. A shy [[beetle]] who, depending on the [[Knight (hollow knight)|]]'s actions, becomes infatuated with them after being rescued [spoilers]and later shifts said attraction to [[Zote]] after he is defeated in the Coliseum of Fools[/spoilers].

title: manjuu_kowai
body: One of the classics of [[rakugo]], wherein people discuss what they are afraid of, and one man who boasts of having nothing to fear confesses that he is actually terrified of manjuu; the denouement is them attacking him with lots of manjuu but he just eating them all and then remarking that what he's [i]really[/i] afraid of is a nice cup of tea.

title: grey_prince_zote
body: Optional boss in [[Hollow Knight]], [b]Grey Prince Zote[/b] is a Dream variant of [[Zote]] [spoilers]fueled by [[Bretta (hollow knight)|]]'s fantasies about him[/spoilers], though significantly more powerful and [[muscular]] than his real self.

title: zote
body:
A recurring character in [[Hollow Knight]], [b]Zote[/b] (a.k.a. [b]Zote the Mighty[/b]) is a traveler who, despite his claims of being a "Knight of Great Renown", regularly requires the [[Knight (hollow knight)|]] to bail him out of dangerous situations.
h4. See also
* [[Grey Prince Zote]]

title: pajamas
body: Any type of clothes designed to be light and comfortable enough to [[sleeping|sleep]] in. This tag encompasses an ensemble consisting of a [[short sleeves|short-]] or [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[shirt]] and either light [[pants]], [[shorts]], or [[capri pants]].

title: circle_formation
body:
Where several characters are shown next to each other in a circular pattern with the length of their bodies pointing towards the center, often headfirst. The "circle" must contain at least three characters, otherwise it might be a [[symmetry]] or [[rotational symmetry]].

h4. See also

* [[weapon formation]]
* [[tag group:posture]]

title: rotational_symmetry
body:
One character positioned upside-down and parallel to another, in a rough approximation of rotational symmetry.

This tag applies to the relative position of two characters, not the image as a whole, and should [b]not[/b] be confused with the sexual position [[69]].

h4.See also

* Origin forum thread: forum #36218
* [[Tag Group:Image composition]]
* [[symmetry]]
* [[circle formation]]

title: charles_babbage_(fate)
body:
Caster-class Servant seen in [[Fate/Grand Order]] first appearing in the [[London (fate/grand order)|]] singularity. A mathematician from 18th century who build the foundation of computer engineering, which leads him to being honored as [b]"Father of the Computers"[/b].

In game, he appears as a bulky, steam-powered [[mecha]] due to surrounding himself [spoiler](his soul)[/spoiler] in a Reality Marble representing his dream of a [[steampunk]] world. [spoiler]Essentially making him a living steam-powered robot.[/spoiler]

title: anyoji_hime
body:
A [[virtual youtuber|virtual school idol]] and member of [[Link! Like! Love Live!]]'s [[Mira-Cra Park!]] from the 104th graduating class. 

She loves video games, particularly shooters, and is also a massive fan of Mira-Cra Park! from long before she herself joined.

She has [[blue eyes]] and [[very long hair|very]] [[long hair|long]] [[pink hair]] that [[gradient hair|tapers off]] to [[blonde hair|blonde]] styled in a [[multi-tied hair|multi-tied]] [[ponytail]] with a [[black ribbon|black]] [[hair ribbon]], [[sidelocks]], [[hair intakes]], and [[blunt bangs|blunt]] [[swept bangs]]. There's also an [[ahoge]] at the base of her ponytail.

She wears an [[open jacket|open]] [[pink jacket|pink]] [[hooded jacket]] with her [[winter uniform|winter]] [[hasu no sora school uniform|school uniform]]. When in her [[summer uniform]], she instead wears a [[white jacket]].

Voiced by [[Kurusu Rin]].

title: hanfu
body:
Historical styles of clothing worn by the Han Chinese. Most styles have a “y” shape collar, but there are also styles with a rounded collar.

There are several styles that are at times mistaken for kimono (most notably [[ruqun]]). You can typically distinguish between them based on the hairstyle and headwear. Males' hair may be pulled back into a simple ponytail or bun or held by a coronet. Emperors or princes may wear [[mian guan]]. If nothing else, [[huadian]] (forehead mark), or the [[tuanshan|circular fan]] is an easy distinguishing mark. 

Hanfu differs from [[Qing dynasty|Qing]] era clothing. Hanfu specifically refers to clothing worn during dynasties wherein the ruling class was made up of the majority Chinese ethnic group, the Han. The Qing Dynasty was ruled by the [[Manchu clothes|Manchu]] ethnic minority. The frog button and mandarin collar style clothes, often simply refered to as Chinese clothes, are not Hanfu, as they are not Han clothing, but in fact Manchu. This goes too for other ethnic minority clothing in china, such as [[Miao clothes]] or [[Uygur clothes]]. These fall under the umbrella of [[Chinese clothes]], along with hanfu.

title: fiona_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Fiona[/b] (フリーダ [i]furida[/i]; [b]Frida[/b]) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

She is the daughter of Lanvega, who was one of Daein's Great Four Riders. She is the ruler of the independent Marado territory in Daein. At first, she sides with the Begnion Occupational Army, but later joins the Daein Liberation Army after seeing what kind of monstrous acts the Occupation Army does to her people. After the last battle, because she is the lady of Marado, she watched over her beloved people and would protect them until the autumn of her years.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Lance Knight

title: super_radiant_peach
body:
The final transformation in [i][[Princess Peach: Showtime!]][/i], given to [[Princess Peach|Peach]] by the power of nearby [[theet_(peach)|Theets]] after [[Grape_(peach)|]] destroys the Sparkle Theater. 

She retains the large crystallized crown, sun-like brooch, and the [[white dress|white]] & [[blue dress|blue]] colors of the [[Radiant Peach]] dress. But instead this dress is similar to [[Rosalina]]'s, losing the puffy short sleeves for [[long sleeves|long]] and [[wide sleeves]]. And while this dress retains the expelling of a [[sparkle]]-like pattern from underneath, the dress itself is also covered with [[print_dress|prints]] of this [[sparkle_print|same pattern]]. 

Known as [b]Super Prism Peach[/b] in Japanese.

* !asset #25505000

body:

She's given a large crystallized crown, her brooch is surrounded by a sun-like pattern, and her dress is turned [[white dress|white]] with the bottom and inner parts being [[blue dress|blue]]. The dress also expels a [[sparkle]]-like pattern from underneath.

Not to be confused with [[neck ribbon]], which is for when a ribbon is used in place of a bowtie or necktie.

title: osawa_rurino
body:
A [[virtual youtuber|virtual school idol]] and member of [[Link! Like! Love Live!]]'s [[Mira-Cra Park!]] from the 103rd graduating class. 

She may seem like an energetic party girl at first, but when she runs out of energy, she goes into what she calls a "dead battery" state. She is childhood friends with [[Fujishima Megumi]].

She has [[blue eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[gradient hair|gradient]] [[blonde hair|blonde]]-to-[[blue hair]]. Her hair is typically put up in [[twintails]] and prominently [[parted bangs]], with a pair of [[white flower|white]] and [[pink flower|pink]] [[hair flower|hair flowers]]. She is often depicted with a single [[fang]]. 

From her third year, she may be seen with what looks like a [[wedding ring]] on her right hand's ring finger. This ring is a parting gift from Megumi.

Voiced by [[Kan Kanna]].

title: kabru
body:
Kabru is a "tallman*" adventurer in [[dungeon_meshi|Dungeon Meshi]]. In many regards, he is the polar opposite of [[laios touden|Laios]]; he has a deep contempt for monsters as a result of [spoilers]being orphaned by a dungeon whose monsters spilled out and killed everyone in his homeland[/spoilers]. He was raised by [[milsiril_(dungeon_meshi)|an elf]] who taught him to be an exceptional fighter, however, that training appears to have only been applicable to human* opponents; he and his party lose frequently to monsters in the dungeon that the ostensibly-less-skilled party lead by Laios handle with relative ease.

[tn]* In Dungeon Meshi, the term "human" applies to many races: halflings, elves, dwarves, gnomes, etc., while the word "tallmen" is used to refer to what most fantasy settings simply call "humans".[/tn]

The majority of his "screentime" thus far has revolved around [spoilers]a time when he and [[Mithrun]] were separated from their respective parties and was forced to care for Mithrun. He consequently learned about the true danger of the dungeon.[/spoilers]

He has [[dark-skinned_male|dark skin]], [[curly_hair|curly]] [[black hair]], and [[green eyes]], and wears a mix of [[leather armor]] and [[chainmail]].

h4. External links
* "Adventurer's Bible entry":[https://mangadex.org/chapter/2c49b74c-aac9-4f4d-b0cd-15117ee839ae]

title: galette_(food)
body:
A term to designate various types of flat round or freeform crusty cakes. It can refer to:
* [b]Fruit galette:[/b] A single crust, free-form [[pie]] with the crust folded partway over the top of the fruit filling. 
* [b]Breton galette:[/b] A [[crepe]]-like dishes in the form of a folded square, originated from Brittany. They are comparatively larger as they are commonly eaten as a main course, and usually filled with savoury ingredients such as [[cheese]], [[egg]] and [[ham]]. 
* [b][[Galette des rois (food)|]][/b]

title: otomune_kozue
body:
A [[virtual youtuber|virtual school idol]] and member of [[Link! Like! Love Live!]]'s [[Cerise Bouquet]] from the 102nd graduating class. 

Former club president of the School Idol Club. She was an honor student well respected around Hasu no Sora, but she is humble. She is bad at technology, but claims she is getting better.

She has [[green eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[purple hair]]. Her hair is typically done up in a [[side ponytail]], [[sidelocks]], and a [[single side bun]] on her right with a [[red flower|red]] [[hair flower]] and [[tassel hair ornament]] on. Sometimes, a [[lone nape hair]] is visible. In her first year at Hasu no Sora, she used to tie her hair in a [[low ponytail]] and had a more serious attitude in contrast with her fellow first-years at the time.

She has graduated from Hasu no Sora along with fellow 102nd year members [[Yugiri Tsuzuri]] and [[Fujishima Megumi]] in March 2025, thus ending her school idol activities at Hasu no Sora. 
Her next goal after graduation is to become a professional composer.

Voiced by [[Hanamiya Nina]].

title: cocoa_bean
body:
Cocoa beans, also known as cacao beans, are the dried and fully fermented [[seed]]s of the Theobroma [[cacao fruit]], native to the tropical regions of Central and South America. They resemble [[coffee beans]] but without the signature slit. 

These beans are the primary ingredient used in the production of [[chocolate]], [[cocoa powder]], and cocoa butter.

title: birdo
body:
[[Mario_(series)|]] character first appearing in [i][[Yume Koujou: Doki Doki Panic]][/i], then later incorporated into the Mario franchise proper with the international version of [i][[Super Mario Bros. 2]][/i]. Birdos were a reoccurring mid-boss and subordinate of [[Wart_(mario)|]] during the attempted conquest of Subcon. Since then however the species has become overall less antagonistic and much more friendlier. 

They are [[reptile_girl|dinosaur-like]] with large snouts in place of a mouth, from which they shoot white [[egg]]s out of to attack. They have long [[eyelashes]], [[eyeshadow]] and wear an [[ornate ring]]. They wear an [[huge_bow|oversized bow]] on the back of their heads as well as have [[claws]].

Birdos come in a variety of colors, though the main color is pink. Compared to [[Toad_(mario)|]]s and [[Yoshi]]s, Birdos are much more consistently represented by a singular individual in a given game, where it's much rarer to see the rest of the species or a multitude in one place.

h4. Official Art
* !post #7938195

* [[Princess Birdo]] ([[Super Crown]]ed)
* [[Striker Birdo]]

title: kamek
body:
[i][[mario_(series)|Mario]][/i] character. 

A [[Magikoopa]] closely associated with [[Bowser]]. He often serves as Bowser's advisor, and has doubled as his caretaker throughout the [i][[super_mario_world_2:_yoshi's_island |Yoshi's Island]][/i] series. He has the ability to make enemies grow.

Not to be confused for the Japanese term for the Magikoopa race. 

Since Kamek and Magikoopas have the exact same design, contextual clues are used to determine one or the other. The image most likely has Kamek if:

** The setting is within the [[Yoshi]] franchise or in the past (such as the main characters are their baby counterparts).
** A [u]singular[/u] [[blue_robe|blue-robed]] Magikoopa that is shown to be closely associated with Bowser, [[Bowser Jr.]] or the [[Koopalings]]
** Has the ability to make characters grow in size
** Rides a broomstick (though some generic Magikoopa does this too)

h4. Official Art
* !post #6077110

* [[Kammy Koopa]]
* [[Princess Kamek]] ([[Super Crown]]ed)

title: koholasaurus_(genshin_impact)
body:
A creature in [[Genshin Impact]].

A type of Saurian found in Natlan. It can freely swim through water, as well as liquid Phlogiston that is as hot as lava. The People of the Springs tribe is most closely associated with them.

Koholasaurs are primarily light blue and black in color with a white underside, as well as some sparse orange pigments. Small fins on the head have orange coloring inside, and black outside. They have a dorsal fin and a long tail. They have two arms and two legs, though these arms are closer to fins for young Koholasaurs.

h1. See also

* [[tepetlisaurus_(genshin_impact)|Tepetlisaurus]]
* [[yumkasaurus (genshin impact)|Yumkasaurus]]
* [[iktomisaurus (genshin impact)|Iktomisaurus]]

* [[tatankasaurus (genshin impact)|Tatankasaurus]]

title: qucusaurus_(genshin_impact)
body:
A creature in [[genshin_impact|Genshin Impact]].

A type of Saurian found in Natlan. They are capable of flight, and can spit fire. The Flower-Feather Clan tribe is most closely associated with them.

Qucusaurs are primarily bright pink and white in color, with red and yellow eyes. They are bipedal, and stand on two [[talons]]. They also have two wings and long tail feathers. Adult Qucusaurs are covered in feathers and have a single [[ahoge]]-like feather on their heads; young Qucusaurs lack these feathers and ahoge.

h1. See also

* [[tepetlisaurus_(genshin_impact)|Tepetlisaurus]]

title: yumkasaurus_(genshin_impact)
body:
A creature in [[Genshin Impact]].

A species of Saurian that lives in Natlan. Yumkasaurs have long tongues that can grapple objects, and they use this ability to eat and swiftly move around. The Scions of the Canopy tribe is most closely associated with them.

Yumkasaurs are primarily green and white in color, with some yellow pigments. They have long ears and a bulky tail they can sit on. Yumkasaurs are bipedal and have two short arms; yellow claws can be found on all four limbs.

h1. See also

* [[tepetlisaurus_(genshin_impact)|Tepetlisaurus]]

title: tepetlisaurus_(genshin_impact)
body:
A creature in [[Genshin Impact]].

One of the species of Saurian living in Natlan. Tepetlisaurs are exceptionally good at digging, and can tunnel through the ground or even up cliffsides. The Children of Echoes tribe is most closely associated with them.

Tepetlisaurs are primarily brown and black in color, with some orange coloring. They are bipedal and have two short arms; all four limbs have claws that are orange or black. They also have a tail.

h1. See also

* [[yumkasaurus (genshin impact)|Yumkasaurus]]

title: iktomisaurus_(genshin_impact)
body:
A creature in [[genshin_impact|Genshin Impact]].

A type of Saurian found in Natlan. They can leap to great heights, glide, have the ability to use Cryo blasts, and have enhanced sensory abilities that allow them to manifest objects from graffiti. The Masters of the Night-Wind tribe is most closely associated with them.

Iktomisaurs are mostly blue and white in color, with blue eyes and orange highlights under their eyes. They have cape-like feathers that extend from their shoulders, used for gliding. They have tall and slender builds, are bipedal, stand on two [[talons]], and have very large ears that extend over the top of their heads.

h1. See also

title: waluigi
body:
[b]Wa[/b]rui ("わるい":[https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E3%82%8F%E3%82%8B%E3%81%84#Japanese], Japanese for bad, evil, etc.) + [b]Luigi[/b] = Waluigi

[[Luigi]]'s self-proclaimed rival. A sly, conceited schemer who secretly trains in order to defeat the Mario Bros, often competing against them in [[playing sports|sporting events]]. Partner in crime with [[Wario]]. 

His trademark appearance is having a [[purple shirt]] with [[long sleeves]] and a [[purple headwear|purple]] [[baseball cap|cap]] that has an upside down "L", along with a very dark [[blue overalls|blue]]/[[black overalls|black]] overalls. He also has [[white gloves]], [[orange footwear|orange]] [[pointy shoes]], a thin angular [[mustache]] and a hooked [[pink nose]].

While thought to be Wario's brother due to early official English material, various later official sources over the years have confirmed that the two have no familial relation.

h4. Official Art

title: acca_howler
body:
Acca Howler (アッカ・ハウラー, Akka Haurā) is currently the main antagonist of the ninth part of the [[JoJo's Bizarre Adventure]] series, [[The JOJOLands]].
Howler is a man with an athletic build. He has [[medium hair]] that is tied back. His hair is voluminous at the top styled in a jelly roll or elephant trunk, albeit with the front gap similar to a heart shape rather than a circle. Howler's beard looks like rectangular strips with gaps in between, going from the sides of his ears to his chin. The top strips of the beard are longer and angled toward his eyes.

He wears a light short sleeve shirt with notch collars, slightly exposing his upper chest. The shirt has a thick dark outline running down vertically from his collars to above the edge of his shirt, with the lines connecting horizontally at the back. His sleeves also have a dark line going across above the edge. He pairs the shirt with light shorts that have checkered hems.
Below his clothes, Howler wears a mesh bodysuit that is dark and semi-transparent with several circular holes. It has long sleeves and covers his arms and legs.
In addition, Howler wears a choker on his neck made of several "H"-shaped emblems, has an "h" emblem shaped like a wolf from his company's logo embedded on his shirt near his abdomen, dark wristbands

title: kingu_(fate)
body:
[[Fate/Grand Order]] character. A god from Babylonian mythology.

He uses [[Enkidu (fate)|]]'s body throughout the Babylonia Singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]], but his personality is markedly different from the original Enkidu's. The only visual difference between Kingu and the regular Enkidu is Kingu's [[purple eyes]], as opposed to Enkidu's [[green eyes]]. And despite retaining the same [[androgynous]] appearance as Enkidu, Kingu is male and is referred to as such by himself and others.

title: dr._eggman
body:
The evil scientific genius known as Dr. Ivo "Eggman" Robotnik is the long-time nemesis of [[Sonic the Hedgehog]]. He's got the master plan, devising many schemes in attempts to destroy Sonic and conquer the world, but he fails 99% of the time; though he's very unpredictable.

He is [[Gerald Robotnik]]'s grandson, and [[Maria Robotnik]]'s cousin, and is also said to possess an IQ of 300.

Voiced in Japanese by [[Ohtsuka Chikao]], Takiguchi Junpei (OVA) and Nakamura Koutarou. Dubbed in English by Deem Bristow), and Mike Pollock. As Dr. Robotnik, he has been voiced by Long John Baldry, Jim Cummings, and Garry Chalk. [[Jim Carrey]] portrays him in the live-action film franchise.
